Description: Complete seal-impression, the fine brown Nile clay has some mica inclusions and was hardened after excavation. The rear shows two sides with each one wide coil of basketry. The top shows an almost complete impression of an oval scarab-like seal with many finger impressions around it. On the left the vertical cartouche of (Mn-kheper-R')|, right of it a kneeling figure with a bow in its hand, facing the cartouche. Another unrecognisable sign above the figure.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
